<tr>
	<td class="alt1" width="175" align="center" valign="top" nowrap="nowrap"><b>Rezz</b>
<span class="smallfont">
	<br />
	Senior Member<br />
		
	
	<br />
	Joined: Aug 2001<br />
	Location: Boston
</span></td>
	
	<td class="alt1" valign="top">
	
	<!-- message -->
	<p>We all know that archery is no longer a <b>highly</b> viable form of primary damage with the recent change to the Hate List (still viable, under certain circumstances).<br />
<br />
Yes, changes to the Hate List, NOT Archery, which many of you seem to cling to.<br />
<br />
Possible issues in Hate List code:<br />
<br />
1) Pre-patch, was there an equation which reduced your generated hate relatice to your distance from the mob, i.e. if you were at max bow range, you generated less aggro than if you were just over minimum?<br />
<br />
If there is a calculation, could that be causing the issues?<br />
<br />
If there is a calculation, could that be backwards now, i.e. you generate more aggro from further away?<br />
<br />
How can this be tested?<br />
<br />
2) Could all arrows, NOT just hits but misses and poofers as well, be generating hate? I am reading in several threads about people being summoned after missing and poofing arrows. <br />
<br />
Could this be causing the tremendous boost in hate?<br />
<br />
This could probably be tested using NON-MAGIC arrows against a target that can only be hit by MAGIC items.<br />
<br />
3) Since I do not use a parser, but we all know that arrow damage is "shown" twice, could the Hate List be doubling our generated hate?<br />
<br />
How could this be tested?<br />
<br />
Please don't just sit and rant here, I'd like to read a thread with data from people testing, suggestions, and brainstorming.</p>
	
	
	
