	<p>One of the guild druids posted that DS damage (non-melee damage) is now attributed to the person with the damage shield (ie, if a mob hits you and takes 100 points of damage from a DS, you gain the same aggro as if you slashed the mob for 100)... I didn't really pay much attention to it, but if it is true, since both spells and archery get a damage and a non-melee damage report, and crit hits get a 3rd report.... Is it possible that maybe aggro generation is reading the damage reports, not the actual damage?</p>
	
	
	
