</span></td>
	
	<td class="alt1" valign="top">
	
	<!-- message -->
	<p>Thank goodness, an effort to identify the problem, now we might get somewhere, thanks Rezz.<br />
<br />
From reading other boards it appears that all classes that do damage from a distance are experiencing very high rates of agro. While this may make playing ping pong fun I would lean towards the guess that range has a place in the equation.  Testing this will be difficult.<br />
<br />
Dalantia's hypothesis seems less likely to me because even pre 60 I am doing at most 250 with a bow.  I get agro when my average shot is between 30-70 while the MT average hit is 50-80.  <br />
<br />
crits I was not watching as closely but it did not seem that getting crits was generating aggro above and beyond what it was before the patch.  In other words given the overall increased agro, crits were drawing agro proportional to regular hits. Similar to agro before the patch. <br />
<br />
I will get a tank and start doing bow damage from various differences.  Over time we should be able to tell if distance is a factor, but I would be hesitant to use data on any less than 10 mobs a close range and 10 mobs at max range due to the high variability of damage. <br />
<br />
I will report what I find.</p>
	
	
	
