</span></td>
	
	<td class="alt2" valign="top">
	
	<!-- message -->
	<p>Spells that get resisted count toward the hate list as if they had done damage, it's possible that arrows that MISS would be counted in the same way as potential damage.  Poofing arrows I don't think would count towards the list since you can fire an arrow at an unaggrod target, have it poof and not gain aggro.<br />
<br />
It would go a long way to explaining why we get so much aggro if the Damage Sheild changes did cause our arrows to be counted twice.  Once for the actual damage, one for the non-melee damage message.  Basically Trueshot would generate 4 times the hate regular archery used to and Jolt just isn't going to cover that.<br />
<br />
All spells counted this way as well would explain extreme caster aggro.  I don't really know how we could test this without access to the actual hate list numbers, but a Dev could test it rather quickly.</p>
	
	
	
