	<td class="alt1" valign="top">
	
	<!-- message -->
	<p>As the Ranger class leader for my guild, obviously this whole thing was something I would bring up, try and get a little brainstorming done.  One of our longstanding members brought this to the table.<blockquote><span class="smallfont">Quote:</span><hr size="1" />I spoke to someone lastnight who works at SOE, the aggro has now been changed not so much in the amount of damage dealt over time, but rather the amount done in one lump sum, in otherwords, even though a warrior may do 20k damage over a few minutes of time, if you throw a nuke on a mob that does 2k damage instantly, you will rise on the hatelist extremely fast. Supposedly they were working on a way the aggro list is handled for more realism, i.e. a mob sees a tank as dinner, but the greater threat is the wizard who can deal 2k in 5 seconds, rather than the warrior who can deal 2k in 10-20 seconds, thus the mob destroys those who can deal damage faster.<br />
<br />
According to him its still in the test phase, and it will be adjusted over time.<hr size="1" /></blockquote>Many of us have been working on the premis that this was a coding error, or something.  This is a different perspective, no matter whether the words themselves are true or not.</p>
	
	
	
