	<td class="alt2" valign="top">
	
	<!-- message -->
	<p>Based on the fact that distance damage dealers, whether they be archers, nukers, or backstabbers standing at max melee are now getting aggro far more often I would say that the change is in the distance hate code.  It used to be a combination of your current proximity to the mob as compared to how much damage you had done (oversimplification but true for normal direct damage.)  Now it appears that the aggro doesn't decrease with distance nearly as much as it traditionally has.  There may be other things going on but this is what it feels like to me playing a ranger and rogue.  It reminds me of the old pre-evade days and not in a good way.</p>
	
	
	
		<div>__________________<br />Aeryll Shadowleaf</div>
	
	
