</span></td>
	
	<td class="alt1" valign="top">
	
	<!-- message -->
	<p>Let's take Verant's logic step by step if what is being said here is true.<br />
<br />
1) If Verant is indeed making it so quick, huge amounts of damage is going to get you up further on the hate list a lot quicker than steady, even damage over time, then the only solution to survivability is to space out your archery/backstab/nuke damage over time, along with whatever aggro mitigation techniques your class has available to you.<br />
<br />
2)  Executing the solution to (1) will produce a rapid reduction in DPS for all groups/raids.<br />
<br />
3)  Obviously, from (2), lowering the effective DPS for everyone will make fights (especially end game fights) last much longer than they already are.  This is the equivalent to giving every boss mob more hitpoints without actually doing so.<br />
<br />
Not only is (3) in direct contrast with a recent change that was made to a few encounters to make them less tedious and more enjoyable (a few of the Luclin encounters, I believe), as well as recent nerfing of modulation rods to prevent clerics from regaining mana more rapidly, (1), (2), and (3) lead me to believe these changes were made for the sole purpose of increasing the overall difficulty of the game after 4 years.  This would be in line with Verant's usual vision that "dramatically increased challenge = more fun".  Or this is one of the first steps in driving all of the EQ addicts to frustration and on to EQ2 to ensure more revenue upon startup.<br />
<br />
It's starting to look more and more like this change was absolutely intentional and may not be broken as we might hope. <img src="images/smilies/frown.gif" border="0" alt="" title="frown" smilieid="2" /></p>
	
	
	
		<div>__________________<br /><img src="http://www.silentambush.com/yendorgladesig.jpg" border="0" alt=""><br />
<a href="http://www.silentambush.com/eqweb/themes.html" target="_blank">THEME MUSIC FOR EVERQUEST</a></div>
	
	
