	<!-- message -->
	<p>I don't have any hard data.  I don't have any first-hand experience, as I haven't been able to group much after the patch.<br />
<br />
I do, however, have a few ideas.<br />
<br />
1) This could be a big mistake.  In removing the limit on the hate list, some of the coding on the mechanics on the list may have been affected.  I'm no programmer, but from listening to the devolpers at Fan Faires, I get the feeling that the coding on the original EQ (including the most basic of game mecanics) resembles a plate of spagetti.<br />
<br />
2) This could be intentional.  It is, after all, a more "realistic" rendering of agro.  It seems, from what I've read, that the mobs are "thinking".  The Warrior standing in front of them is NOT the biggest threat, the people standing away from it doing massive damage and the people keeping the Warrior alive are.  <br />
<br />
I'm not about to stop playing the game, nor am I about to stop playing my Ranger.  It may be time for us all to sit around the table with some beer and figure out a new way to kill stuff, however.  It may be a whole new game.</p>
	
	
	
