<tr>
	<td class="alt2" width="175" align="center" valign="top" nowrap="nowrap"><b>Genuvien</b>
<span class="smallfont">
	<br />
	Senior Member<br />
		
	
	<br />
	Joined: Sep 2000<br />
	
</span></td>
	
	<td class="alt2" valign="top">
	
	<!-- message -->
	<p>My money is on something that has happened before - a reversed sign.<br />
<br />
Think about it...we have seen some spells and effects that rather than ADDING mana or health have actually SUBTRACTED.<br />
<br />
Suppose that the distance component was added and expanded to include ALL damage, but for some reason, the mitigator was reversed, so that damage from a person in close melee range generates less aggro than equal damage from somebody at a distance because the formula HATE = DMG*(1/DISTANCE) actually was coded as HATE = DMG*DISTANCE.<br />
<br />
Stranger things have happened.  And this would explain the summoning of players who cause damage from a distance, and 'might' even help to explain summoning on misses if you assume a non-zero default DMG number for misses (for example you can generate aggro with a miss - as I have done pulling).</p>
	
	
	
	
	
