	<td class="alt1" valign="top">
	
	<!-- message -->
	<p>Just got done testing the distance theory, that is for recap, how far away from the mob you when dealing damage is part of the hate list equation.  To test this I took my shaman and ranger to EW to pull rygor elites.<br />
<br />
I pulled them to the front of the rygor fort with snare, once the were at the east edge the shaman would slow and sic pet on them. Ranger would then either:<br />
1. Get just outside of melee range to plink arrows.<br />
2.  Go to the far side of the fort (near CC zone out) and plink arrows from there. <br />
<br />
Bow was twisted longbow, buffs were consistent for all pulls, ranger had no procs on the orc, Shaman did no damage. <br />
<br />
I killed 10 at close range and 10 at long range.<br />
<br />
Aggro was the same for both.  somewhere between the 10th and 20th arrow aggro shifted from the pet to me.  <br />
<br />
The goal of this test was to see if distance from the mob influenced hate list equation, and since results did not change with range I can assume distance is not part of the equation. <br />
<br />
Anyone else testing this?</p>
	
	
	
