	Joined: Jan 2002<br />
	
</span></td>
	
	<td class="alt2" valign="top">
	
	<!-- message -->
	<p>Ok, been lurking for a while, but decided to come back for this one. I have to say that is is not an archery nerf but in general a fubar in the aggro system. <br />
<br />
Right after server up I went as to Bastion of Thunder as a 63 ranger EQ/AM3 with Obsidian Compound bow and Mithril champ arrows. <br />
<br />
Waited for a Vindi Militis (warrior mob) to be taken to 50% by a group, paladin tanking. Only mob in camp so it was not mezzed,charmed etc.<br />
<br />
One arrow at 50% on mob, dmg was 312 non crit and the Militis came right for me, even tho I was at max distance.  How in the heck can you pull aggro off a paladin who has been chain stunning for half of it's life is beyond me. <br />
<br />
Next test- logged in as 65 rogue. Summoned throwing daggers, 250 throwing skill. Again Vindi Militis, same group, threw a deadly strike of 65 at max range. Mob was at 50% when I crit, turned and ran straight for me. <br />
<br />
In a normal xp group with a paladin tanking we did a few experiments. Mezzed mob, (Crystaline golem) Paladin does 5 stuns in a row, then breaks mez. I allow Paladin to melee it to 92% then join in fight. Just with a backstab of 430 (non crit) the mob turns on me and proceeds to wail me to death. Evade will not break aggro, and all I did was one backstab. <br />
<br />
I haven't logged in since. Only thing I can postulate is that aggro is being calculated by type of damage, and new modifiers have been assigned to each type, ie dmg shields have their own aggro mod now, melee another and range another. <br />
<br />
I've never said this before, but allowing this obvious bug to last will definatly drive people off the game.</p>
	
	
	
	
	
