	<p>I know that I am too low to have the problems you guys are facing, but I see what you are saying.  But it really makes sense to me.  When you attack a mob, and get an add.  Who do you kill first?  Depends on the mob right?  Now say there is a gnoll in HHP that you pull.  He is regular old melee monster.  Now your add is a shaman, he stays a little ways back, and starts casting on you.  Who do you go after?  The shaman, he has less hp's but does more dmg, and helps his friend do more dmg with his spells (debuffs and such).  Seems to me it is a little AI at play here.  <br />
<br />
However, I also see this as being seriously debilitating to rangers as a class.  As I have joked with many friends about, rangers without a bow are just a buff.  We are a dmg shield/rune effect.  It's almost a joke that they are nerfing out archery this much.  Thank the lord I am so low I am still a tank in most groups <img src="images/smilies/smile.gif" border="0" alt="" title="smile" smilieid="1" /></p>
	
	
	
	
	
