	<p>After reading a number of the threads (and this one is the best), I had what may be an interesting thought.<br />
<br />
What if aggro is also dependent upon positiong relative to the mob?<br />
<br />
i.e. a Rogue BEHIND the mob.<br />
<br />
Makes sense in RL.  Someone stabs me in the back I'm turning around real quick.  Obviously, something was changed with ranged damage too, whether it is related to the non-melee message I'm not sure.  But what if you had a Ranger/Caster doing damage from afar BEHIND the mob?  Insta-summon.<br />
<br />
Honestly, they probably threw in a bunch of modifiers, shook it up and said, "Come on Baby!  Come on with that Yo!"<br />
<br />
Looks to me like they crapped out.</p>
	
	
	
	
	
