<tr>
	<td class="alt1" width="175" align="center" valign="top" nowrap="nowrap"><b>Neetero</b>
<span class="smallfont">
	<br />
	Senior Member<br />
		
	
	<br />
	Joined: Sep 2001<br />
	
</span></td>
	
	<td class="alt1" valign="top">
	
	<!-- message -->
	<p>Something just occurred to me after fighting in PoV at OC last night...I had very very few aggro problems.  The night before (right after the patch) I had all sorts of aggro problems at EW in PoV and doing south camp in BoT.  Now that I think about it, I saw another post on our boards that someone else had absolutely no problems with aggro at OC camp in PoV.  A friend of mine was doing IC camp and also had no problems at all with aggro. <br />
<br />
So consider this: Could the aggro issues be mob or camp specific?  This would explain why everyone is getting conflicting results.  <br />
<br />
What I think we need to do is try to summarize all of the camps, mobs, zones where aggro problems are happening (blatently obvious) and try to isolate them from those camps that no one is reporting problems with.  This will expedite our testing and may help SOE determine the root cause of the problem.<br />
<br />
Has anyone had problems with caves in PoV?<br />
Has everyone had problems with giants in BoT?<br />
What about boss mob encounters?  Which ones are fubered?<br />
<br />
I think if we focus on this, we'll start to see a pattern materialize...</p>
	
	
	
